00:36:35.163 --> 00:36:36.324 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<c.bg_transparent>I won't discuss it with you.</c.bg_transparent>

624
00:36:37.357 --> 00:36:38.350 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<c.bg_transparent>As for Enina Tandro</c.bg_transparent>

625
00:36:39.344 --> 00:36:42.927 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<c.bg_transparent>yes, I feel the shame</c.bg_transparent>
<c.bg_transparent>of Curzon's indiscretion.</c.bg_transparent>

626
00:36:44.560 --> 00:36:47.206 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<c.bg_transparent>When one of my kind stumbles, Benjamin,</c.bg_transparent>

627
00:36:47.539 --> 00:36:49.421 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<c.bg_transparent>it is a mistake that's there forever.</c.bg_transparent>

628
00:36:50.398 --> 00:36:53.220 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<c.bg_transparent>I can't tell you which part of Curzon Dax</c.bg_transparent>

629
00:36:53.996 --> 00:36:57.359 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<c.bg_transparent>couldn't stop himself from acting</c.bg_transparent>
